
üß† Memory & RAM Commands

free -h                         # Show total, used, free RAM and swap in human-readable format
free -m                         # Display memory usage in MB
free -g                         # Display memory usage in GB
cat /proc/meminfo               # Detailed kernel memory statistics
vmstat                          # Show memory, swap, CPU, and I/O statistics
vmstat 5                        # Refresh memory stats every 5 seconds
top                             # Real-time process memory usage
htop                            # Enhanced interactive memory and process viewer
ps aux --sort=-%mem             # List processes sorted by memory usage
ps -eo pid,comm,%mem,%cpu       # Show memory and CPU usage per process
watch free -h                   # Continuously monitor memory usage

====================================================================================================

üîÑ Swap Memory Commands


swapon --show                   # Show active swap devices/files
cat /proc/swaps                 # List swap usage details
free -h | grep Swap             # Quick swap usage summary
vmstat | grep si                # Show swap-in activity
vmstat | grep so                # Show swap-out activity
cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness     # Check system swappiness value


======================================================================================================

üîç Per-Process Memory & Swap Usage

smem                            # Show per-process memory and swap usage (best tool)
smem -s swap -r                 # Sort processes by swap usage
pmap <PID>                      # Show memory map of a process
pmap -x <PID>                   # Detailed memory usage of a process
grep VmRSS /proc/<PID>/status   # Show resident memory of a process
grep VmSwap /proc/<PID>/status  # Show swap used by a specific process

================================================================================================

üìä System Memory Pressure & Health

uptime                          # Show load average (memory pressure indicator)
dmesg | grep -i oom             # Check for Out-Of-Memory killer events
slabtop                         # Kernel slab memory usage
sar -r                          # Historical memory usage (sysstat)
sar -S                          # Historical swap usage




=================================================================================================

‚öôÔ∏è Kernel & Memory Tuning

sysctl -a | grep vm             # Show all VM-related kernel parameters
sysctl vm.swappiness            # Check swappiness setting
sysctl vm.overcommit_memory     # Check memory overcommit policy
sysctl vm.overcommit_ratio      # Check overcommit ratio

=================================================================================================

üìÅ Memory-Related Files & Paths

/proc/meminfo                   # Main memory statistics file
/proc/swaps                     # Swap device/file information
/proc/<PID>/status              # Per-process memory & swap info
/proc/sys/vm/                   # Kernel memory tunables
/etc/sysctl.conf                # Persistent memory tuning config
/etc/fstab                      # Swap mount configuration


==================================================================================================

